Sales Data Analysis During Diwali in India

This Jupyter Notebook performs an exploratory data analysis (EDA) on Diwali
sales data to identify customer purchasing patterns, product performance
trends, and key business insights across different demographic segments.

The analysis includes data cleaning, preprocessing, descriptive statistics,
and visualization-driven insights using Python, Pandas, Matplotlib, and Seaborn.

ðŸŽ¯ Objectives of the Analysis

- Understand customer demographics and purchasing behaviour
- Compare spending across gender, age groups, and marital status
- Identify high-performing states, occupations, and customer segments
- Analyze top-selling product categories and product IDs
- Generate insights to support retail business decision-making

ðŸ§° Tools & Libraries

- Python, Jupyter Notebook  
- Pandas, NumPy  
- Matplotlib, Seaborn  

ðŸ“Š Key Insights Covered

- Gender-wise and age-group-wise spending trends  
- State-wise and occupation-wise sales contribution  
- Marital status vs purchase behaviour  
- Product category sales performance  
- Top 10 products by amount and order volume 
